OL,3,CAntarctica: Following Shackleton's
OL,4,CEndurance mission 100 years on
OL,6,FNo British research ship has been this
OL,7,Ffar south at this time of year since
OL,8,F1915, as ITV News' Science
OL,9,FCorrespondent Martin Stew explains
OL,11,FWe've been in the Antarctic Circle for
OL,12,Fthree weeks now. Each day, we edge
OL,13,Fcloser to midwinter, as the thickening
OL,14,Fsea ice inches toward us.
OL,16,FOur next stop is Elephant Island, at
OL,17,Fthe northern end of the Antarctic
OL,18,FPeninsula.
