OL,3,CAntarctica: Following Shackleton's
OL,4,CEndurance mission 100 years on
OL,6,FBack on the bridge, Captain Will and
OL,7,Fhis team keep watch 24 hours a day.
OL,8,FEven when stationary, bergs can drift
OL,9,Fin from any direction.
OL,11,FIn Antarctica, midwinter's day is a
OL,12,Fbig deal. I'm incredibly lucky to be
OL,13,Fcelebrating it south of 60 degrees
OL,14,Flatitude onboard a British research
OL,15,Fship for the first time in more than a
OL,16,Fcentury.
OL,18,FI just hope our journey home will be a
OL,19,Flittle smoother and a lot quicker than
OL,20,FShackleton's crew experienced.
